cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GT

The paper deals with the problem of approximating two-dimensional shapes using discrete assembly systems, which involves combinatorial and geometric aspects. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also involves the use of algorithms and complexity analysis, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, the paper discusses the NP-hardness of the problem, which is a topic in cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper involves the use of Zometool construction kit, which is related to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
